The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Mumbai, Oct. 14: Mahanagar Telephone Nigam Ltd (MTNL) has rolled out the countrys first IPTV service in Mumbai, enabling subscribers to access digital television services through the Internet. The service will be commercially launched on Diwali (October 21), MTNL chairman and managing director R.S.P. Sinha said here today. The state-run telecom company has entered into a strategic tie-up with IOL Broadband Ltd for the service, which will be available for Rs 199 per month.

 Mumbai, Oct. 14: Indias forex reserves came down by $30 million to $165.275 billion during the week ended October 13 from $165.305 billion during the week ended October 6. The reserves had decreased by $1.177 billion during the preceding week. The foreign currency assets decreased by $30 million to $158.310 billion during the week.

 New Delhi, Oct. 14: The Asian Development Bank (ADB) will extend a $100-million loan to India to strengthen the commodity derivatives markets, a senior government official said.




